Tignon (sometimes tinyon).

A woman's head covering of cloth.  Sometimes as simple as a bandana tied so as to cover the hair, sometimes quite elaborate.

In the early 19th. century, women of color, including creol, mestizo, metis and mulatto were required to cover their hair with a tignon when in public as a mark of subserviance. The use of the tignon by women of color may have been the result of pressures brought to bear by ugly white women.